%U A396486 8,16,4,4,8,4,16,2,2,4,8,4,4,8,8,4,8,2,2,4,4,12,12
%N A396486 Irregular triangle read by rows: T(1,1) = T(2,1) = 1; for n >= 3, the n-th row lists the number of Dirichet characters chi modulo n such that Q(chi) = Q(zeta_(2d)) for each divisor d of psi(n)/2, where Q(chi) is the field generated by the values of chi, and psi = A002322 is the reduced totient function.
%C A396486 For n >= 3, let d is the k-th divisor of psi(n)/2. If d is odd, then T(n,k) is the number of elements in (Z/nZ)* having order d or 2*d; otherwise T(n,k) is the number of elements in (Z/nZ)* having order 2*d.
%H A396486 Jianing Song, <a href="/A396486/b396486.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..9887</a> (rows 1..1500)
%H A396486 Jianing Song, <a href="/A395473/a395473.txt">List of Q(chi) for characters chi modulo n <= 2048</a>.
%H A396486 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dirichlet_character">Dirichlet character</a>.
%e A396486 Table begins
